reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Sanders is incredibly knowledgeable and passionate about biology. Her lectures are engaging and well-structured.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Prof. Chen is an outstanding teacher. He explains complex concepts clearly and is always available for extra help.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson's course content is interesting, but her lectures can be a bit disorganized at times.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Prof. Williams makes math enjoyable. His problem-solving techniques are very helpful.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Lee's enthusiasm for chemistry is contagious. Her lab sessions are particularly well-designed and informative.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Brown seems knowledgeable, but his lectures are often dry and monotonous.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Taylor's analysis of literary works is insightful. She encourages critical thinking and class discussions.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Prof. Martinez covers the material well, but sometimes rushes through difficult concepts.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Wong's classes are thought-provoking and relevant. She relates theoretical concepts to real-world issues effectively.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Prof. Wilson has a great teaching style. He uses practical examples to illustrate economic principles.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Dr. Davis is very knowledgeable, but her grading can be inconsistent and unclear at times.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Thompson's lectures are engaging and he encourages healthy debate on political issues.

reviews.subject: Neuroscience
reviews.review: Dr. Garcia is an excellent educator. She breaks down complex neurological concepts into understandable parts.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Prof. Kim's assignments are often unclear, and he doesn't provide enough guidance on course expectations.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Green is passionate about environmental issues. Her field trips add great value to the course.

reviews.subject: Mechanical Engineering
reviews.review: Prof. Lee is knowledgeable but can be impatient with students who struggle with the material.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Dr. Martinez makes linguistics fascinating. Her interactive teaching methods are highly effective.

reviews.subject: Business Administration
reviews.review: Prof. White brings real-world business experience to the classroom. His case studies are particularly insightful.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Patel's course content is interesting, but her lectures can be hard to follow at times.

reviews.subject: Electrical Engineering
reviews.review: Prof. Nguyen is excellent at explaining complex circuits. His lab sessions are well-organized and informative.
